&gt; Misunderstood, probably RTFM (Reda The F***ing Mail) syndrome 
&gt; on my part.
&gt; What I think is the issue is that you should have an abstract 
&gt; test case
&gt; AbstractEnhancedTextfieldTest that contains all testXxx() 
&gt; methods and an
&gt; instance variable of type JTextfield. Then make concrete subclasses
&gt; (ChildATest, ChildBTest,...), in the setUp you instantiate 
&gt; the correct one:
&gt; 
&gt; public class ChildBTest extends AbstractEnhancedTextfieldTest {
&gt;     public void setUp(){
&gt;         setMyTextfield(new ChildA());
&gt;     }
&gt; }
&gt; 
&gt; and then in the TestSuite:
&gt; 
&gt;  	public static Test suite()
&gt;  	{
&gt;  		TestSuite suite = new TestSuite();
&gt;  
&gt;  		suite.addTest(new TestSuite(ChildATest.class));
&gt;  		suite.addTest(new TestSuite(ChildBTest.class));
&gt;  		return suite;
&gt;  	}
&gt; 
&gt; Even nicer would be to use a factory method in the concrete children.
